The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of spectral expander graphs suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The explicitness and discreteness properties of the matrix A may also relate to the field of symbolic computation (cs.SI).
